Title: How to build mini high voltage Jacob's Ladder
Description:
Today's build is really simple but really cool looking miniature high voltage Jacob's ladder. 
In this video we assemble "15KV high voltage generator kit", get some basic working principles about Jacob's ladder and maybe some more general tips and tricks.
Heart of the build is cheap 15KV high voltage generator kit, i bought it online for about 1.5.- USD.
Total budget on parts was around 2..3USD :)
You can run it on single 18650  battery but i chose dc jack (At the moment the prices of batteries are too high).

Intro: (0:00)
Working principle: (0:28)
Parts: (0:41)
Kit assembly: (0:51)
Step-up transformer: (2:23)
Kit test: (3:33)
Enclosure: (3:52)
Copper wire: (4:26)
Soldering: (5:17)
Assembly: (6:46)
Outro: (8:04)


 Step by step guide:
---------------------------------------------------------
https://www.instructables.com/id/Mini-High-Voltage-Jacobs-Ladder/

Here are the main components i used for this build:
---------------------------------------------------------
High voltage generator kit - https://www.aliexpress.com/item/32968528180.html?spm=a2g0s.9042311.0.0.27424c4d1FbJ5f
Momentary push button - https://www.aliexpress.com/item/32850618919.html?spm=a2g0s.9042311.0.0.27424c4dYGrDbZ
DC jack - https://www.aliexpress.com/item/32973509798.html?spm=a2g0s.9042311.0.0.27424c4dIHBi6m
Ring Crimp Terminals/Connectors - https://www.aliexpress.com/item/32697753272.html?spm=a2g0s.9042311.0.0.27424c4dhXE4y5
Pin Screw Terminal - https://www.aliexpress.com/item/4000935638574.html?spm=2114.12010615.8148356.6.10646d58wsJZpr

Scrapped copper wire, plastic lids, some nuts and bolts.
---------------------------------------------------------

Caution! High voltage can be deadly! This project is not a toy, do not built his project without prior knowledge of electrical or fire safety. Do not touch or correct output wires while device is powered.
All videos are shot using smartphone Xiaomi mi k20/t9.

Thank you for your view, i hope you liked my video and learned something new! Feel free to share, comment, like and subscribe:)

Title: Go Fuzz Yourself! Where do I even begin?! – MIKE CURNOW
Description: For those who are unfamiliar with the term or practice of Fuzz Testing, it’s essentially the combination of testing input validation coupled with stress testing, which is performed by spraying inputs of a target device, application, or system with random and crafted input at high velocity and observing the effects on the target. Use cases can involve testing input forms on a website to ensure it doesn’t accept foreign or script characters or ensuring that IIoT devices are programmed to be functionally robust.
